<p>
  <span class="nym">Lombard</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Late Latin</span> <i>Longobardus</i>, <i>Langobardus</i> 'Lombard', lit. 'long beard', derived from <span class="lang">Proto-Germanic</span> *<i>langaz</i> 'long' + <span class="lang">Proto-Germanic</span> *<i>bardaz</i> 'beard'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The Langobards were a Germanic tribe who invaded Italy in the 6th C.  The use of this term as a personal name reflects a trend in late-medieval/early Renaissance Italy for ethnic descriptives as given names.</p>
  
  


